{
  "text": "In this section, we define a set of parameters which measure the effective-length of an encoding function. We consider general Boolean functions, and find a decomposition of these functions into components which operate over specific subsets of the input sequence. The proposed decomposition builds upon the analysis in [CITATION_1] . The first subsection summarizes the well-known results. The second subsection contains some new results (Proposition 1 and 3).",
